str2: Probably from the same as pale; anew, i.e. back, once more, or furthermore or on the other hand.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: From apo and stello; set apart, i.e. to send out literally or figuratively.
Other, another (of more than two), different. A primary word; 'else, ' i.e. Different.
(a) (as adj.) enslaved, (b) (as noun) a (male) slave. From deo; a slave.
Or neuter pleion, or pleon comparative of polus; more in quantity, number, or quality; also the major portion.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
First, before, principal, most important. Contracted superlative of pro; foremost.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: (a) I make, manufacture, construct, (b) I do, act, cause. Apparently a prolonged form of an obsolete primary; to make or do.
In like manner, likewise, just so. From hos and an adverb from autos; as thus, i.e. In the same way.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Dative Masculine 3rd Person Plural
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
